
# 📘 COLLECTIONS FRAMEWORK 

---

# 🧠 1️⃣ What is Collections Framework?

## ✅ Definition

The **Collections Framework** is a set of classes and interfaces used to **store, manipulate, and manage groups of objects dynamically**.

---

## 🎯 Why Collections?

👉 Problem with arrays:

* Fixed size ❌
* No built-in methods ❌

👉 Collections solve:

* Dynamic size ✅
* Ready-made methods ✅
* Better performance handling ✅

---

# 🧱 2️⃣ Collection Hierarchy (IMPORTANT)

```
Collection (interface)
   |
   |---- List
   |       |---- ArrayList
   |       |---- LinkedList
   |
   |---- Set
   |       |---- HashSet
   |       |---- TreeSet
   |
   |---- Queue
           |---- PriorityQueue
```

👉 Map is separate (not part of Collection)

---

# 🧾 3️⃣ LIST (ORDERED + DUPLICATES ALLOWED)

---

## 🔹 ArrayList (MOST USED 🔥)

### ✅ Features

* Dynamic array
* Allows duplicates
* Maintains order

---

## 💻 Code

```java
import java.util.*;

public class ArrayListDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ArrayList<String> list = new ArrayList<>();

        list.add("Java");
        list.add("Python");
        list.add("Java");

        System.out.println(list);
    }
}
```

---

## 🔥 Interview Points

👉 Internal:

* Uses **dynamic array**
* Default size = 10
* Resize = 50% increase

---

---

## 🔹 LinkedList

### ✅ Features

* Doubly linked list
* Fast insertion/deletion

---

## 💻 Code

```java
LinkedList<Integer> list = new LinkedList<>();
list.add(10);
list.add(20);
```

---

## 🔥 Interview Difference

| Feature | ArrayList | LinkedList |
| ------- | --------- | ---------- |
| Access  | Fast      | Slow       |
| Insert  | Slow      | Fast       |

---

# 🧾 4️⃣ SET (NO DUPLICATES)

---

## 🔹 HashSet

### ✅ Features

* No duplicates
* No order

---

## 💻 Code

```java
HashSet<Integer> set = new HashSet<>();

set.add(10);
set.add(20);
set.add(10);

System.out.println(set); // duplicate removed
```

---

## 🔥 Interview Points

👉 Uses:

* Hashing
* O(1) operations

---

---

## 🔹 TreeSet

### ✅ Features

* Sorted
* No duplicates

---

## 💻 Code

```java
TreeSet<Integer> set = new TreeSet<>();
set.add(30);
set.add(10);
set.add(20);

System.out.println(set); // sorted
```

---

# 🧾 5️⃣ MAP (KEY-VALUE) 🔥🔥

---

## 🔹 HashMap (MOST IMPORTANT 🔥🔥🔥)

### ✅ Features

* Key-value pairs
* Unique keys
* Fast (O(1))

---

## 💻 Code

```java
import java.util.*;

public class HashMapDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        HashMap<Integer, String> map = new HashMap<>();

        map.put(1, "Jay");
        map.put(2, "Ram");

        System.out.println(map.get(1));
    }
}
```

---

## 🔥 Internal Working (INTERVIEW GOLD)

👉 Uses:

* Hashing
* Bucket array
* Linked list / tree (Java 8+)

---

# 🧠 HashMap Flow

```
Key → hashCode() → index → store value
```

